The evidence with the title 'Nearly half of Britons pay no income tax as burden on rich increases ' says Apr 26, 2016  ... The Institute For Fiscal Studies said that the proportion of working - age adults who do not pay income tax has risen from 34.3 per cent to 43.8 per cent, equivalent to 23million people . Over the same period the amount of income tax paid by the richest 1 per cent has risen from 24.4 per cent to 27.5 per cent ,  ... 
